This article, written in 2015 when President Muhammadu Buhari became President, is reproduced below for some relevance to the goings-on in Nigeria of 2018 Augean Stables By Ademola Adegbamigbe Muhammadu Buhari who was sworn in as President of Nigeria on 29 May 2015 has a Herculean task ahead of him. In fact, he needs to transform himself into Hercules of Greek mythology to succeed. Hercules was commissioned by Augeans, king of Elis, to help him clean his dirty stables which, for over 30 years, had never been touched.   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.